ğŸŒ Purpose

v149.x keeps the Federated Continuum in motion.
Instead of a one-time synchronization, each node of the Codex now performs a heartbeatâ€”periodic verification and reconciliation with its peers.
It is the collective self-healing layer of the entire network.


---

ğŸ§  Core Functions

1. Heartbeat Verification

Every node runs scripts/federate.py --heartbeat, fetching peer lineage and consensus.

A cron or CI workflow ensures this executes hourly or daily.



2. Consensus Reconciliation

If divergences appear, a repair proposal is generated: federated_repair.json.

Once â…” of peers sign off (future ED25519 signature threshold), the consensus root updates.



3. Cross-Node Healing

Damaged or missing manifests are restored from the majority-agreed lineage.

The self-healing property of v148.x now extends network-wide.



4. Federated Learning Hooks

AI Ã— TI Ã— NI synthesis used to model network health, latency, and truth stability.

These metrics update versions/temporal.json â†’ health_index.





